SEO consultancy offers flexibility, good income, and intellectually engaging work.

## What Does an SEO Consultant Do?

Audit websites, identify ranking opportunities, create strategic roadmaps, and guide implementation. Consultants provide strategic direction whilst clients handle implementation.

## Essential SEO Skills to Develop

Technical SEO competency, content strategy expertise, analytics and reporting, and communication skills.

## How to Be an SEO: Career Progression

Stage 1: Learn fundamentals (3-6 months). Stage 2: Gain practical experience (6-18 months). Stage 3: Develop strategic thinking (18-36 months). Stage 4: Build consultancy (Year 3+).

## Freelance SEO Rates: UK Market

- Junior (1-2 years): £25-40/hour, £400-800/month retainer
- Mid-level (2-5 years): £50-80/hour, £1,000-2,500/month retainer
- Senior (5+ years): £80-150/hour, £2,500-10,000+/month retainer
- Niche specialist: £100-200+/hour, £5,000-20,000+/month retainer

## Pricing Models Explained

Hourly, project, retainer, and value-based pricing. Primarily uses project and retainer pricing.

## Common Beginner Mistakes

Underpricing services, overpromising results, lacking clear service definitions, not documenting work, targeting wrong clients.

## Building Your First Clients

Leverage existing network, create portfolio projects, content marketing, and specialisation advantages.

## Tools and Investments

Minimum tool investment: £100-150/month. Comprehensive setup: £300-500/month.

## Realistic Income Expectations

Year 1: £1,500-3,000/month full-time. Year 2: £3,000-6,000/month. Year 3+: £6,000-15,000+/month. Top consultants earn £200,000+/year.

## The Reality Check

Requires continuous learning, managing client expectations, delivering results in competitive markets, and business development. Genuinely rewarding work with good income potential.
